Ordered on Uber. Downtown Roll has progressively gotten worse. I’ve been a regular, but the last few times sushi has definitely gone down hill. If you even want to call it sushi. The salmon doesn’t look like salmon; it’s shredded white/light pink pasty substance. Almost like they are using imitation salmon and trying to pass it off as the real thing. I’ve kept this place in mind for a while and been a regular due to the low price, but I’m beginning to wonder what I’m actually eating and why it’s being advertised as something else. Over the time period I have been ordering, I have also watched the Downtown Roll shrink significantly in size. It would appear that there is some cost cutting going on and it’s very apparent in the quality of the food. I noticed that the roll has become mostly rice, with a really tiny avocado and whatever you want to call this salmon stuff that doesn't even have the flavor of salmon. I really hope REAL quality sushi gets used in the future in a place that advertises having real sushi. In the event that the owner would like to respond to the declining quality over the last 3 months and commit to improvements, I'd give it one last try. But until then, I'm skeptical and will order sushi elsewhere.

This is my go-to place for lunch. I love that you can customize your rolls from top to bottom, there are so many different choices of veggies and sushi meats, and their selection of dipping sauces never fails to impress me. Their bibimbap is PHENOMENAL if you're not into sushi - it's a rice bowl with thinly sliced Korean bbq beef, spinach, shiitake mushrooms, and other vegetables. I highly, highly recommend a custom roll with the traditional wrap, avocado and cucumber, shrimp tempura and spicy tuna, sesame seeds, and wasabi mayo; with an eggroll on the side.  Another reason why I love this place is because it's a Mom-n-Pop shop, and everybody remembers your order and name if you come often. I think the customer service is great, they always thank you for coming and I normally don't wait any longer than 5 minutes for my food. Prices are definitely reasonable.  It makes me really annoyed to see reviews from customers who don't know what they're talking about - if you don't like their food, you probably have poor taste in foods in general. If you complain about the time it takes, you probably shouldn't go during the lunch rush, just like anywhere else in Downtown during that hour.

If you want to try something different skip the sushi and order the Bibimbap (bi-bim-bap)! It's a Korean dish that's kind of like mix-it-up-yourself fried rice loaded with veggies and a seasoned meat, you can skip the meat and go just with the veggies too. I recommend ordering an egg on top and using the chili sauce. When you get the dish everything will be separated into little piles on top of the rice with the fried egg on top, simply take the chili sauce an pour it on top then mix and mash everything together! Once it's all mixed real good, enjoy!  I usually fill up after eating half then take the rest home for dinner or a snack, not a bad deal for $9 and it's good Korean food. My husband, who is Korean, found this and told me about it. I'll add a pic of everything mixed up, there's the egg, seasoned meat (kind of sweet), spinach, cucumber, zucchini, bean sprouts and carrot.
